what works:
    - basic shell commands
    - pipes
    - output and input redirection
    - background jobs
    - handling SIGINT to kill shell commands but not the shell
      process itself

additional extensions:
    - commands with multiples pipes, combinations of redirection,
      pipes and backgrounds, etc.
    - shell prints info about background tasks
        - i.e. numbering background tasks and background job
          pids (similar to bash)
        - displays exit info when background jobs complete
